cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM

This paper deals with the problem of synthesizing realistic images from human drawn sketches, which is a topic that falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and computer graphics (cs.GR). The proposed approach uses a Generative Adversarial Network (GAN), which is a popular technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper introduces a new building block for the generator and discriminator, which is a technical contribution that could be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) research.
